    <div class="section firstReview">
      

<div id="review_236139272" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/236139272" />
    <a title="Nicole" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4578380-nicole"><img alt="Nicole" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442625247p2/4578380.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/236139272?book_show_action=true">Nov 16, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nicole" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nicole" href="/user/show/4578380-nicole">Nicole</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Older teens and young adults</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Nicole by: </span>
      r2r
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4578380-nicole?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4578380-nicole?shelf=sci-fi">sci-fi</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4578380-nicole?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4578380-nicole?shelf=free-read-for-review">free-read-for-review</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer236139272" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11394998169324934477">Well now...<br/><br/>What an odd funny little book.<br/><br/>I am really glad I finished it, I came very close a couple of times to putting it down. The only reason I probably didn’t is my OCD and my inability to let things go. But I really am glad I finished it!<br/>Lucy is a typical teenager except she is dead, right off the bat John Corwin kills most of his characters. They. Are. All. Dead. LOL! So the book is about their afterlife and discovering what killed them. Can’t say I ever read another story like this before</span>
  <span id="freeText11394998169324934477" style="display:none">Well now...<br /><br />What an odd funny little book.<br /><br />I am really glad I finished it, I came very close a couple of times to putting it down. The only reason I probably didn’t is my OCD and my inability to let things go. But I really am glad I finished it!<br />Lucy is a typical teenager except she is dead, right off the bat John Corwin kills most of his characters. They. Are. All. Dead. LOL! So the book is about their afterlife and discovering what killed them. Can’t say I ever read another story like this before. I don’t read science fiction and thought through the first half of the book that this story was not for me, but somehow Corwin sucks you in with his characters eccentricities. <br /><br />I liked how well he blended modern dialog and terminology into the story without sounding like an old guy trying to sound hip. That being said I do think Mr. Corwin needs a little more insight as to how a teenage girls mind works if he is going to write from their perspective. I would suggest to the author to attend a Justin Bieber concert followed by a midnight showing of breaking dawn and why don’t you just round out the night with some all night “boy talk” ;-)<br /><br />Overall it was a fun read! Thank you to the brave John Corwin for offering his work up for review and to the Paranormal Romance &amp; Urban Fantasy Fanatics! Group on goodreads!<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11394998169324934477" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


