<div id="review_236988375" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/236988375" />
    <a title="Jennifer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6288631-jennifer"><img alt="Jennifer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1329319478p2/6288631.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/236988375?book_show_action=true">Nov 18, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennifer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennifer" href="/user/show/6288631-jennifer">Jennifer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer236988375" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5987809968397907795">The Next Thing I Knew by John Corwin was a very unique and interesting read. From the very first page it begins with Lucy waking up to realize that everyone in the entire world has died. Everyone she know now exists only as ghosts. They are in a new realm where they can pretty much do whatever they want. They can visit any places on earth, in space, or in the new realm that they now live in. Lucy and her friends find it fun in the beginning, but then they try to find out how it is possible that </span>
  <span id="freeText5987809968397907795" style="display:none">The Next Thing I Knew by John Corwin was a very unique and interesting read. From the very first page it begins with Lucy waking up to realize that everyone in the entire world has died. Everyone she know now exists only as ghosts. They are in a new realm where they can pretty much do whatever they want. They can visit any places on earth, in space, or in the new realm that they now live in. Lucy and her friends find it fun in the beginning, but then they try to find out how it is possible that everyone in the world could have died at the same time. <br /><br />I really enjoyed this story. I would consider it more of a science fiction book than a paranormal romance. The story is very unique and kept my attention. The story had just a little romance in it, however I think it would have been just fine without it. The romance between Lucy/Chris wasn't very developed, maybe because you don't get to know Chris that much as a character. The story had many plot twists that I wasn't expecting. Very good, enjoyable read.<br /><br /> </span>
  <a data-text-id="5987809968397907795" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


